1
00:00:09,833 --> 00:00:11,133
Now,

2
00:00:11,267 --> 00:00:14,933
we are not just
welcoming a colleague.

3
00:00:15,667 --> 00:00:18,233
We are celebrating Samuel.

4
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:23,700
A loyal, brave, and kind man.

5
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:26,533
You risked your life for my son,

6
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:30,033
and I will be forever grateful
to you.

7
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:34,433
Thank you, sir, for those, uh...
 kind words.

8
00:00:34,633 --> 00:00:35,833
That's enough talking.

9
00:00:35,967 --> 00:00:37,333
Come on, let's have a toast.

10
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:41,167
Cheers!

11
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:43,633
Everyone, meet Danny.

12
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:46,600
He's one of the many scam
victims of Mike Trinidad.

13
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:49,000
W-What's the problem, Danny?

14
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:50,900
The loan shark
I owed money to--

15
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:53,733
You thought you could hide
from us?

16
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:55,167
- Oh my!
- Goodness!

17
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:57,100
I'm working myself to the bone
just to pay you back!

18
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,600
- Oh no!
- Good grief!

19
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:00,267
I'll repay you soon!

20
00:01:03,867 --> 00:01:05,067
Watch your back, Danny!

21
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:06,733
We'll get you one of these days!

22
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,133
Dude, to be honest,

23
00:01:09,233 --> 00:01:11,267
I'm not sure I feel comfortable
 with your plan.

24
00:01:11,367 --> 00:01:13,467
This was the only way
I could think of

25
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:17,033
to scrounge up enough evidence
against them.

26
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:19,100
Don't worry.

27
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:21,367
I've got people backing me up.

28
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:22,467
"It's ready."

29
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:23,633
Uh, sir?

30
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,333
We received a mission order

31
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:28,133
from the National
Revenue Authority.

32
00:01:28,233 --> 00:01:32,167
They will be conducting an audit
 at Oriental Ridge.

33
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:33,767
What?!

34
00:01:33,867 --> 00:01:35,000
An audit?

35
00:01:35,167 --> 00:01:36,200
When?

36
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:38,433
It's confirmed
for tomorrow, sir.

37
00:01:38,533 --> 00:01:39,367
Alright.

38
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:40,933
I'll just have a talk
with Jacob.

39
00:01:41,067 --> 00:01:42,867
Not all of these records
are clean.

40
00:01:43,033 --> 00:01:45,033
You think that's news
to me, Jacob?

41
00:01:46,533 --> 00:01:48,500
How could you drop the ball
on this?

42
00:01:48,667 --> 00:01:51,667
We need someone
to launder our money!

43
00:01:51,833 --> 00:01:53,833
If Mike were alive,

44
00:01:53,933 --> 00:01:55,900
he would've figured it out!

45
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:57,167
Uh, excuse me.

46
00:01:57,267 --> 00:01:59,533
Is there a problem, sir?

47
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:04,300
I heard the NRA will conduct
an audit here.

48
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:07,733
Sir, taxation is one of my areas
 of expertise.

49
00:02:07,867 --> 00:02:09,667
I can help you.

50
00:02:14,767 --> 00:02:21,600
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

51
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:41,767
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:45,733
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

53
00:02:56,933 --> 00:03:03,767
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

54
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:17,367
Taxation is one of my areas
of expertise.

55
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,567
How can you help us?

56
00:03:22,267 --> 00:03:23,400
Well, first,

57
00:03:24,267 --> 00:03:27,933
I need to know whether they'll
uncover any discrepancies.

58
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:29,267
[SNICKERS]

59
00:03:29,433 --> 00:03:31,967
If so, you need to show me
your books.

60
00:03:32,133 --> 00:03:34,767
[JACOB CHUCKLES DRYLY]

61
00:03:34,867 --> 00:03:36,167
He's lost his mind.

62
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:37,433
Is this a joke?

63
00:03:37,533 --> 00:03:41,167
Sir, I'm not going to find
anything they won't.

64
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:42,400
If there are any discrepancies,

65
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:45,000
it's better that
I see them first.

66
00:03:45,133 --> 00:03:46,100
So I can fix them.

67
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:49,767
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

68
00:03:49,867 --> 00:03:52,133
What are you hiding?

69
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:54,767
Whatever it is, I can help.

70
00:03:54,967 --> 00:03:56,433
I can protect you.

71
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:01,200
You just need to trust me.

72
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:03,000
I'm on your side, Sir Roldan.

73
00:04:03,167 --> 00:04:05,300
Sir, you can trust me.

74
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:06,667
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

75
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:09,800
Remember, I took a bullet
for your son.

76
00:04:12,233 --> 00:04:13,933
And I will take a bullet
for you.

77
00:04:14,033 --> 00:04:15,667
I can clean up any mess.

78
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:21,800
[HUFFS]

79
00:04:21,967 --> 00:04:28,767
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

80
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:36,833
Land acquisitions,

81
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:40,367
project expenses,
list of contractors--

82
00:04:40,533 --> 00:04:42,000
- Everything's on your desk.
- Okay.

83
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:45,033
This one.

84
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,500
Three disbursements for
land development in Tanauan

85
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:50,833
but no supporting permits
or progress reports exist?

86
00:04:51,767 --> 00:04:55,033
This book has inconsistent
posting of entries.

87
00:04:55,767 --> 00:04:58,167
The auditor might
become suspicious

88
00:04:58,267 --> 00:04:59,633
of the overlapping dates.

89
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,333
And regarding this contractor...

90
00:05:02,467 --> 00:05:03,833
They received a hefty sum,

91
00:05:03,933 --> 00:05:06,000
more than a hundred
million pesos,

92
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:08,867
but the details of their
supposed project are missing.

93
00:05:09,033 --> 00:05:10,567
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

94
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:13,700
Sir, I've just begun scratching
 the surface here.

95
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,400
And I'm sure tons
of discrepancies

96
00:05:15,567 --> 00:05:16,833
are waiting to be uncovered.

97
00:05:17,533 --> 00:05:19,367
So what?
Can you fix them or not?

98
00:05:21,467 --> 00:05:23,833
- Of course I can.
- There we go.

99
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:27,367
[ROLDAN SIGHS IN RELIEF]

100
00:05:27,467 --> 00:05:33,700
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

101
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:34,967
[KNOCKING ON THE DOOR]

102
00:05:35,933 --> 00:05:37,067
Sir?

103
00:05:37,167 --> 00:05:41,200
Here's the list of transactions
 that might be flagged.

104
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:43,200
Each has its own memo.

105
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:44,967
A narrative, a justification.

106
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,067
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

107
00:05:48,167 --> 00:05:50,233
This one includes the report on
the land acquisition in Tanauan.

108
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:53,300
I reclassified it as
speculative development.

109
00:05:53,433 --> 00:05:55,100
I also prepared
a feasibility study

110
00:05:55,267 --> 00:05:56,867
and an internal appraisal.

111
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,400
This folder contains the delays
 in the books.

112
00:06:00,167 --> 00:06:02,533
I justified them as part
of a system transition.

113
00:06:02,633 --> 00:06:04,733
We'll say we changed
our accounting software,

114
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:06,967
which caused a mix-up
in the entries

115
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,100
during migration.

116
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:12,100
I created reconciliation tables
to make it look more believable.

117
00:06:12,267 --> 00:06:13,600
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:06:13,767 --> 00:06:15,433
Oh, and sir, here's the one
regarding the contractor.

119
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,600
I filed it as a CSR project.

120
00:06:18,767 --> 00:06:21,100
Corporate Social Responsibility.

121
00:06:21,267 --> 00:06:22,900
We'll present it
as if we hired them

122
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,800
for a community
development initiative

123
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:28,267
where Oriental Ridge
pledged a donation.

124
00:06:28,433 --> 00:06:31,133
I also prepared a project brief
 and a Memorandum of Agreement

125
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:33,433
to support it.

126
00:06:33,533 --> 00:06:37,100
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

127
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,433
Sir,

128
00:06:38,533 --> 00:06:41,667
I've discovered numerous
unexplained earnings

129
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:44,000
amounting to hundreds
of millions.

130
00:06:45,167 --> 00:06:47,967
It could become a major issue
if the NRA uncovers them.

131
00:06:52,667 --> 00:06:55,533
But don't worry,
I'm already working on it.

132
00:06:55,667 --> 00:06:57,600
I'm currently creating
paper trails.

133
00:06:57,700 --> 00:07:00,867
Contracts, records of donations,
 dummy projects.

134
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,000
Everything to make it appear
they came from legal sources.

135
00:07:04,167 --> 00:07:05,367
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

136
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:07,467
Good. Carry on.

137
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,800
[SAMUEL] Okay. Thank you, sir.

138
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,033
[SAMUEL GRUNTS SOFTLY]

139
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:13,800
[ROLDAN] Samuel.

140
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:18,500
Aren't you going to ask where
all that money came from?

141
00:07:20,533 --> 00:07:23,133
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

142
00:07:23,233 --> 00:07:24,300
No, sir.

143
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,867
It's not my place to ask.

144
00:07:27,567 --> 00:07:31,000
I'm here to fix the problem.

145
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:34,167
Excuse me, sir.

146
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:41,833
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

147
00:07:41,933 --> 00:07:44,000
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

148
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,167
[PRINTER WHIRRING]

149
00:07:56,767 --> 00:08:00,033
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

150
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:06,700
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,833
[BEKKAH] So where is
 the morning tea coming from?

152
00:08:11,133 --> 00:08:18,000
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

153
00:08:32,167 --> 00:08:33,967
Sir, everything's ready.

154
00:08:34,767 --> 00:08:38,367
I've written memos
explaining every discrepancy.

155
00:08:38,467 --> 00:08:39,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

156
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:41,233
- Are you sure?
- Yes, sir.

157
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:43,033
You have nothing to worry about.

158
00:08:43,967 --> 00:08:44,933
Crisis averted.

159
00:08:46,433 --> 00:08:47,567
I'll get going now.

160
00:08:51,767 --> 00:08:53,067
- [SIGHS DEEPLY]
 - Roldan.

161
00:08:53,167 --> 00:08:54,100
[JACOB INHALES SHARPLY]

162
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,767
Do you think he actually
pulled it off?

163
00:08:56,933 --> 00:08:58,400
Swept everything under the rug?

164
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:01,600
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

165
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:02,833
I guess so.

166
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:05,567
But if he actually did,

167
00:09:06,967 --> 00:09:08,833
then he's even better
than his dad.

168
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:10,933
[SCOFFS]

169
00:09:12,133 --> 00:09:14,000
- [DOOR OPENS]
- [BEKKAH] Sir, excuse me.

170
00:09:14,133 --> 00:09:14,933
Um...

171
00:09:15,033 --> 00:09:17,167
The people from the NRA
are here.

172
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:18,933
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

173
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,267
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

174
00:09:21,667 --> 00:09:24,000
We're here to collect
your books.

175
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,833
Sure. We are ready.

176
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,100
We have nothing to hide.

177
00:09:33,967 --> 00:09:40,967
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

178
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:44,933
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

179
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:54,300
Please send my thanks
to Colonel Enrico.

180
00:09:54,467 --> 00:09:56,133
For contacting his assets
in the NRA.

181
00:09:56,233 --> 00:09:57,600
It's been a huge help.

182
00:09:57,700 --> 00:10:00,133
Roldan and his brother
are absolutely rattled.

183
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:01,267
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

184
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,667
You created a problem

185
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:06,833
just so you could come in
and fix it.

186
00:10:06,933 --> 00:10:08,833
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

187
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,467
Do you think this will work?

188
00:10:10,567 --> 00:10:12,533
That you'll become one of them
after this?

189
00:10:13,533 --> 00:10:14,633
Yeah.

190
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,667
I'm in.

191
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:22,733
Roldan doesn't know it
yet, but...

192
00:10:24,067 --> 00:10:25,200
I'm already in.

193
00:10:25,367 --> 00:10:32,167
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:10:48,367 --> 00:10:54,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

195
00:10:56,733 --> 00:10:59,167
[ENRICO BREATHES DEEPLY]

196
00:11:01,467 --> 00:11:02,433
How was it?

197
00:11:02,933 --> 00:11:04,333
All good, sir.

198
00:11:04,433 --> 00:11:06,867
Samuel can now
join Roldan's inner circle.

199
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:10,067
Thanks for your help
with the NRA.

200
00:11:10,233 --> 00:11:11,300
[CHUCKLES]

201
00:11:11,433 --> 00:11:12,633
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

202
00:11:12,767 --> 00:11:13,767
I have to say...

203
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:15,033
[CLICKS MOUTH]

204
00:11:15,167 --> 00:11:16,900
I'm impressed with Samuel.

205
00:11:18,167 --> 00:11:19,900
He's smart and resourceful.

206
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:23,967
And above all,
he has a true criminal mind.

207
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:27,467
Sir, do you think...

208
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:29,633
that's an advantage?

209
00:11:29,767 --> 00:11:34,433
If you aim to catch a criminal,
you must think like one.

210
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:36,367
You need...

211
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,800
a criminal mind, too.

212
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:44,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

213
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:51,233
[LINE RINGING]

214
00:11:51,333 --> 00:11:53,567
- Hello, Samuel?
- [UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

215
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:55,233
You didn't come home last night.

216
00:11:55,367 --> 00:11:56,467
Are you okay?

217
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,567
Yes, Ma.

218
00:11:58,667 --> 00:11:59,667
Uh...

219
00:12:00,467 --> 00:12:02,000
I just had a lot of work to do.

220
00:12:02,133 --> 00:12:04,267
Son, I'm still not comfortable

221
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:06,567
with you working
at that company,

222
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:08,767
especially with
your criminal bosses.

223
00:12:09,933 --> 00:12:11,067
I know, Ma, but...

224
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:12,900
don't worry.

225
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:15,600
I've got this.

226
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:18,033
I know what I'm doing.

227
00:12:18,167 --> 00:12:19,033
Are you safe, son?

228
00:12:19,167 --> 00:12:22,167
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:23,667
I am, Ma.

230
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:24,333
That's what...

231
00:12:24,467 --> 00:12:25,833
I'm working on right now.

232
00:12:27,067 --> 00:12:29,933
[WHISPERS] So they won't be
a danger to us anymore.

233
00:12:30,067 --> 00:12:31,467
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

234
00:12:31,633 --> 00:12:33,333
- Samuel.
- Sir?

235
00:12:33,467 --> 00:12:36,167
- [LINE DISCONNECTS]
- Hello? Hello?

236
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:37,167
[SAMUEL CLEARS THROAT]

237
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:38,600
The NRA called.

238
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:42,333
They're requesting
supporting documents

239
00:12:42,467 --> 00:12:44,967
for the issues you flagged.

240
00:12:45,133 --> 00:12:47,000
Yes, sir. It's...

241
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:48,000
all sorted out.

242
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:52,800
You're good, Samuel.

243
00:12:54,233 --> 00:12:55,367
Thank you, sir.

244
00:12:57,200 --> 00:13:04,033
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

245
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:08,400
Everyone at the cafe misses you.

246
00:13:10,533 --> 00:13:12,067
I miss them, too.

247
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:15,200
I've been wanting to come in,
but Luke insists I rest.

248
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:16,867
I'll be reporting tomorrow.

249
00:13:18,033 --> 00:13:21,200
Oh, I guess I didn't need
to bring food.

250
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:22,833
You've got so much here.

251
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:25,600
Papa brought that over
yesterday.

252
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:27,733
We were supposed to eat it,

253
00:13:27,867 --> 00:13:30,067
but he had to rush out
because of an emergency.

254
00:13:31,433 --> 00:13:32,400
So...

255
00:13:32,867 --> 00:13:35,367
he made time for you, but...

256
00:13:35,533 --> 00:13:36,833
he ran out of time?

257
00:13:37,633 --> 00:13:38,833
Yeah, pretty much.

258
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:41,400
At least...

259
00:13:42,233 --> 00:13:43,000
he's trying.

260
00:13:44,133 --> 00:13:45,167
But...

261
00:13:45,733 --> 00:13:46,767
I had to get shot first.

262
00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:50,000
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

263
00:13:50,133 --> 00:13:51,000
Enzo...

264
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:53,567
How well do you know
your father?

265
00:13:54,767 --> 00:13:56,600
[CHUCKLES]
What kind of question is that?

266
00:13:56,733 --> 00:13:58,800
Obviously, I know my father.

267
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:01,567
He's been my father since birth.

268
00:14:02,900 --> 00:14:04,367
Just asking.

269
00:14:04,467 --> 00:14:07,100
I never knew my father,
you see.

270
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:08,033
That's all.

271
00:14:08,167 --> 00:14:15,033
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,100
You're weird.

273
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:20,033
Let's just eat.

274
00:14:20,967 --> 00:14:23,467
Why didn't you heat up
the food from the fridge?

275
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,633
Because I knew you were coming.

276
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:32,567
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

277
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:35,633
[PHONE BUZZING]

278
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:37,567
[SAMUEL] Agnes?

279
00:14:37,667 --> 00:14:39,933
[AGNES]
 Samuel, where are you?

280
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:41,067
I just went out for air.

281
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:46,767
I need to clear my head
for my next step.

282
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:48,433
[AGNES] Is that so?

283
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,667
Alright, take care.

284
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:53,567
- [BODY THUDS]
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

285
00:14:53,667 --> 00:14:55,933
- Hey!
- Hey! Stop!

286
00:14:59,100 --> 00:15:05,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

287
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:09,133
[TRAFFIC NOISE]

288
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:12,100
My landlady
just wouldn't let me.

289
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:16,200
I can't even go to my parents
because they're mad me.

290
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:19,300
You can stay with us if you
still haven't found a place.

291
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:20,833
- Really?
- Yes.

292
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,533
Thank you.

293
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:26,933
Our struggles never seem to stop
because of that Mike Trinidad.

294
00:15:27,033 --> 00:15:29,433
If I run into any
of his family...

295
00:15:29,533 --> 00:15:31,000
I'll make them pay!

296
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:37,167
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

297
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:40,733
I'll give them a 360-degree
head spin when I see them!

298
00:15:40,867 --> 00:15:42,167
[ARISSA] Hi again, Ms. Cruz.

299
00:15:42,267 --> 00:15:44,233
I'm sorry if I'm bugging you

300
00:15:44,367 --> 00:15:46,733
but please reply
once you see this message.

301
00:15:46,867 --> 00:15:48,167
[PHONE CHIMES]

302
00:15:48,267 --> 00:15:50,167
Especially that Arissa.

303
00:15:50,267 --> 00:15:52,533
That Arissa who went viral!

304
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:55,400
[ARISSA] I want to fix
 the mess Dad caused.

305
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:57,033
I know you've been dragged
into all this.

306
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,900
I also want to help you.

307
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:01,400
- Oh!
- That's her!

308
00:16:01,533 --> 00:16:02,667
That's really her!

309
00:16:02,767 --> 00:16:04,167
- She's pretty, huh.
- The nerve!

310
00:16:04,267 --> 00:16:07,967
See? That girl looks so good
because of our money!

311
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:11,533
[WOMAN] She's wasting our money
to look that good!

312
00:16:11,633 --> 00:16:12,700
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

313
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:13,833
[ENZO] She's a good person.

314
00:16:13,933 --> 00:16:16,533
I feel sorry for her

315
00:16:16,633 --> 00:16:19,567
because she's been dragged
into her dad's mess.

316
00:16:20,967 --> 00:16:23,867
Why didn't you tell Arissa
about our group?

317
00:16:24,033 --> 00:16:25,867
She's already dealing
with so many problems.

318
00:16:25,967 --> 00:16:28,400
I don't want to add more
to her burden.

319
00:16:28,567 --> 00:16:30,867
[WOMAN] I just want to pull
her hair, beat her up

320
00:16:30,967 --> 00:16:32,067
and drag her off!

321
00:16:32,233 --> 00:16:33,933
[BEBINA] I'll squeeze her nose!

322
00:16:34,067 --> 00:16:35,333
I'm dead serious!

323
00:16:35,433 --> 00:16:38,367
- Look at her other video!
- That spoiled brat!

324
00:16:38,467 --> 00:16:40,500
Hey. Why are you
just standing here?

325
00:16:41,967 --> 00:16:44,033
It's just hot. Uh...

326
00:16:44,133 --> 00:16:45,733
Take a seat, Pa.

327
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:47,200
Go on.

328
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:51,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

329
00:16:51,567 --> 00:16:52,700
Oh my god.

330
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:54,567
She's seen my message.

331
00:16:54,733 --> 00:16:57,067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

332
00:16:57,233 --> 00:16:59,067
[ARISSA] Ms. Cruz, I know
 you've read my message.

333
00:16:59,233 --> 00:17:00,700
Please reply.

334
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:04,067
Please. I want to know
about my father's victims.

335
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:05,700
I want to help them.

336
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:11,733
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

337
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:13,100
- Hey!
- Hey!

338
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:14,633
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [GRUNTING]

339
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:15,767
Stop!

340
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:18,467
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

341
00:17:18,633 --> 00:17:20,767
Come here!
You can't run away from us!

342
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,600
You think someone
will defend you here?!

343
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:23,800
Please have mercy on me.

344
00:17:23,867 --> 00:17:25,167
- Have mercy?!
- [BLOW LANDS]

345
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:27,133
[SAMUEL] Stop! That's enough.

346
00:17:27,267 --> 00:17:29,400
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

347
00:17:29,533 --> 00:17:30,600
Enough?

348
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:32,333
You also want a beating?!

349
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:34,567
[MAN 1] Get lost.
This is none of your business.

350
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:35,900
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GRUNTS LOUDLY]

351
00:17:36,033 --> 00:17:37,500
[GRUNTS LOUDLY, WAILS]

352
00:17:37,667 --> 00:17:39,900
- [MAN 2] Who's that? Hit him!
- [GRUNTS IN PAIN]

353
00:17:40,033 --> 00:17:41,833
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GRUNTING IN PAIN]

354
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:42,933
Enough!

355
00:17:43,033 --> 00:17:46,333
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

356
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,100
Let's talk calmly.
What's the problem?

357
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:51,067
Talk calmly?
That guy owes us so much!

358
00:17:51,233 --> 00:17:53,167
And he's telling us
he has no money to pay?!

359
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:55,133
I didn't know Yayaman Tayo
was an investment scam.

360
00:17:55,233 --> 00:17:58,200
I put all the money there.

361
00:17:58,367 --> 00:17:59,133
Investment?

362
00:17:59,233 --> 00:18:01,267
- You bastard!
- Stop!

363
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:02,367
That's enough!

364
00:18:02,533 --> 00:18:08,767
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [GROANING WEAKLY]

365
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:11,167
How much does he owe you?

366
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:12,633
Half a million pesos.

367
00:18:12,733 --> 00:18:13,967
Half a million pesos?

368
00:18:14,067 --> 00:18:21,167
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

369
00:18:26,167 --> 00:18:28,967
Call me.
I'll pay off his debt.

370
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:30,367
With interest?

371
00:18:31,767 --> 00:18:32,967
Yes.

372
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:36,967
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

373
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,700
This is what I have for now.

374
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:41,733
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

375
00:18:41,867 --> 00:18:43,133
Now, go.

376
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:45,533
Go. Just call me.

377
00:18:45,667 --> 00:18:46,733
Go!

378
00:18:47,767 --> 00:18:49,000
That's enough.

379
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:50,533
- Come on.
- Let's go.

380
00:18:50,667 --> 00:18:57,500
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

381
00:18:58,133 --> 00:18:59,433
Are you okay?

382
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:01,500
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

383
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:03,733
You and your father
are to blame for this!

384
00:19:05,367 --> 00:19:08,833
Because of you two,
I'm neck-deep in debt!

385
00:19:08,967 --> 00:19:12,433
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

386
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:16,267
Even if you pay off my debt...
[SNIFFLES]

387
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:19,100
You can no longer fix the mess
you and your father caused.

388
00:19:19,233 --> 00:19:20,700
You ruined my life!

389
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:22,533
And everyone else's lives.

390
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:25,100
Yes!

391
00:19:25,267 --> 00:19:27,033
There are many of us!

392
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,733
All our lives got ruined
because of you!

393
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:32,733
I'm meeting them today.

394
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:34,767
Now, what do I tell them?

395
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:36,800
"My problem's over!"

396
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:41,300
"Samuel Trinidad
will pay off my debt!"

397
00:19:42,967 --> 00:19:44,133
Like that?

398
00:19:44,267 --> 00:19:46,600
- [MUSIC BECOMES EMOTIONAL]
- [SNIFFLES]

399
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:48,600
How about them?

400
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:51,933
How about them?!

401
00:19:52,067 --> 00:19:59,100
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

402
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:02,933
- Mm.
- Help yourselves.

403
00:20:03,133 --> 00:20:04,600
Thank you.

404
00:20:05,967 --> 00:20:06,733
[GASPS]

405
00:20:06,833 --> 00:20:08,100
- Danny! Oh my gosh!
- Danny! Danny!

406
00:20:08,367 --> 00:20:10,633
Did those goons catch you?!

407
00:20:10,767 --> 00:20:12,467
What happened to you, huh?

408
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:21,000
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

409
00:20:21,167 --> 00:20:23,467
- What are you doing here?
- Please calm down.

410
00:20:23,933 --> 00:20:25,767
I didn't come here
to cause trouble.

411
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:29,300
I know you're angry
with me and my family.

412
00:20:29,833 --> 00:20:31,233
I don't blame you.

413
00:20:32,133 --> 00:20:34,267
But I just want to apologize

414
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:36,333
for what my father did to you.

415
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,000
[SCOFFS]

416
00:20:39,067 --> 00:20:40,500
Oh, he apologized,

417
00:20:40,833 --> 00:20:43,367
so I guess we can
all just move on, huh?

418
00:20:44,467 --> 00:20:46,000
It doesn't work like that!

419
00:20:46,967 --> 00:20:49,167
Take a look at
what happened to Danny!

420
00:20:50,633 --> 00:20:53,133
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

421
00:20:53,233 --> 00:20:56,300
I know it doesn't
fix everything.

422
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:59,667
I get it if you don't want
to forgive me.

423
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:01,833
But please believe me,

424
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:08,000
all I want is to fix
what my father did to you.

425
00:21:08,733 --> 00:21:11,700
I can't return
all of your money yet,

426
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:14,067
but I'll do whatever I can,

427
00:21:14,233 --> 00:21:15,500
step by step,

428
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:16,867
until I make it right.

429
00:21:20,100 --> 00:21:23,133
Write down all your names

430
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:26,733
and the amount
my father took from you.

431
00:21:26,900 --> 00:21:28,633
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

432
00:21:28,733 --> 00:21:29,833
Write it all down.

433
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:33,233
Every cent.

434
00:21:33,867 --> 00:21:35,000
Go ahead.

435
00:21:35,533 --> 00:21:36,233
List your names.

436
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,133
Well, if you said so.

437
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:43,000
There's nothing left
to lose anyway.

438
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:55,267
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

439
00:22:07,733 --> 00:22:08,933
Thank you.

440
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:14,200
I give you my word,

441
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,700
I will give back
all of your money.

442
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,567
I just hope
you won't let us down.

443
00:22:23,067 --> 00:22:24,100
I'll get going.

444
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:26,633
I'm sorry.

445
00:22:26,767 --> 00:22:33,467
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

446
00:22:35,567 --> 00:22:37,633
[SAMUEL]
 They are your victims, Roldan,

447
00:22:38,167 --> 00:22:40,100
along with the countless others
 you've deceived.

448
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:43,267
I can't give
their money back yet.

449
00:22:43,433 --> 00:22:44,933
Not now.

450
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:47,733
I need this chance
to get inside your circle

451
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:49,567
and destroy it from the inside

452
00:22:49,700 --> 00:22:52,600
to make sure
you can't ruin another life.

453
00:22:53,367 --> 00:22:55,067
And when my mission is done,

454
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:58,233
I'll return every cent you took

455
00:22:58,333 --> 00:23:00,433
and help them rebuild
the lives you destroyed.

456
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:04,567
If it weren't for Samuel,
we'd be done for!

457
00:23:04,700 --> 00:23:06,467
You want to bring him
into our circle?!

458
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,600
Samuel can work around
the law for us.

459
00:23:08,700 --> 00:23:11,633
A new scam is
about to be launched.

460
00:23:13,333 --> 00:23:14,767
Who didn't hit the quota?!

461
00:23:15,933 --> 00:23:19,100
- [WHIMPERS] Have mercy, sir!
- [BLOWS LANDING]

462
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:23,067
Samuel's got Roldan
by the throat.

463
00:23:24,067 --> 00:23:26,533
I know you ordered
the kidnapping of my son.

464
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:28,600
What do you want?
